OL,3,CIrregular employment of migrant
OL,4,Cworkers falls following new laws
OL,6,FThis move has been welcomed by NGOs
OL,7,F(non-governmental organisations), who
OL,8,Fhave long stressed the need to support
OL,9,Fworkers to stay in legal employment
OL,10,Feven when forced to leave because of
OL,11,Fpoor conditions.
OL,13,FIn 2023, almost 31,000 employment
OL,14,Fpermits were issued with almost 40,000
OL,15,Fin the previous year. This compares
OL,16,Fwith around 16,400 per year in the
OL,17,Fperiod 2019-2021.
